casebody.data:
Daniel E. AUGUST
v.
Darrell VANNOY, et al. NO. 2018-KH-0213 Supreme Court of Louisiana. February 11, 2019

WRIT NOT CONSIDERED. Petitioner has not demonstrated that he sought review in the court of appeal before filing in this Court nor shown the "extraordinary circumstances" that would justify bypassing that level of review. La.S.Ct.R. X § 5(b).
